TEXT(beginproblem());
$showPartialCorrectAnswers = 0;

$d = random(2,6,2) ;

BEGIN_TEXT

Let \( T_{$d}(x) \) be the sixth degree Taylor polynomial of the function
\( f(x) = \cos(x) \) at \(a = 0 \). Suppose you approximate	\( f(x) \) by \( T_{$d}(x) \). If \( |x| \leq 1 \), what is the bound for your error of your estimate? 
$BR$BR
$BITALIC Hint: use the alternating series approximation. $EITALIC $BR$BR

Answer:  \{ans_rule(20)\}

END_TEXT



ANS(num_cmp("1/fact($d+2)"));

ENDDOCUMENT();        # This should be the last executable line in the problem.
